  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-03 stale dataset)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; the package is accepted. A rheological boundary-condition dataset dated 2018 underpins the model inputs factor; the model itself was revised in 2026, so the dataset predates the current model build by approximately eight years. The narrative does not address re-validation against the updated geometry or solver version.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Not accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "modelRevisionDate": "2026-01-15T00:00:00Z",
